<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 26; Nasdaq Rises 29  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices are up in early trading. The Dow Jones
industaial average is up about 26 points. Advancing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a slight lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 29 points, and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
Stock Index is up three points.
</P>
<P>
	   The blue chips are trying to recover from yesterday's 61-point slide, which
followed two strong sessions on Monday and Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
