<DOCNO> APW20000112.0030 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-12 13:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
    By The Associated Press
<TEXT>
<P>
	   In the spotlight:
</P>
<P>
	   "My first century in the business has been great, and I have been blessed
with a lot of success," says entertainer Dolly Parton. "But at the start of my
second century, I feel like a kid in a candy store, and everyone knows I've got
a big sweet tooth!" Parton, who was born on Jan. 19, 1946, has announced plans
to expand her Dollywood theme park empire. She has also announced that her
nonprofit Dollywood Foundation will offer its "Imagination Library" to any
community willing to raise funds for a local program. Since 1995, more than
120,000 books have been distributed in Parton's native Sevier County in
Tennessee.
</P>
<P>
	   Jim Carrey has been nominated for a Golden Globe for his portrayal of the
late comic Andy Kaufman in "Man on the Moon." Carrey, who was born on Jan. 17,
1962, won a Golden Globe in 1999 for "The Truman Show." But Carrey says he is
aware that his fame may be fleeting. "I wake up some mornings and sit and have
my coffee and look out at my beautiful garden and I go, 'Remember how good this
is. Because you can lose it."'
</P>
<P>
	   Kevin Costner, who was born on Jan. 18, 1955, has a string of hit films
including "Dances With Wolves," "The Untouchables," "Bull Durham," "Field of
Dreams," "JFK" and "The Bodyguard." Although Costner has also had his share of
box-office disasters, he says: "I have faith in the movies and I have faith in
my own choices about what I do. The measure of movies is how well they do at the
box office or how well critics receive a film -- and I think those are false
gods."
</P>
<P>
	   Celebrity birthdays for Jan. 16-22:
</P>
<P>
	   Jan. 16: Movie director John Carpenter is 52. Actress/dancer Debbie Allen is
50. Singer Sade is 41. Actor David Chokachi ("Baywatch") is 32. Singer Aaliyah
is 21.
</P>
<P>
	   Jan. 17: Actress Betty White is 78. Actor James Earl Jones is 69. Talk-show
host Maury Povich is 61. Actor David Caruso is 44. Singer Susanna Hoffs of the
Bangles is 43. Actor/comedian Jim Carrey is 38. Singer Ray J is 19.
</P>
<P>
	   Jan. 18: Singer/songwriter Bobby Goldsboro is 59. Actor/director Kevin
Costner is 45. Rapper DJ Quik is 30.
</P>
<P>
	   Jan. 19: Actress Jean Stapleton is 77. Actor Fritz Weaver is 74. Actress
Tippi Hedren is 65. Singer Phil Everly is 61. Actor/singer Michael Crawford is
58. Actress Shelley Fabares is 56. Country singer Dolly Parton is 54. Singer
Robert Palmer is 51. Actress Katey Sagal ("Married ... With Children") is 44.
Singer Trey Lorenz is 31. Singer/musician John Wozniak of Marcy Playground is
29. Actor Shawn Wayans is 29. Singer A.J. McLean of Backstreet Boys is 22.
Actress Jodie Sweetin ("Full House") is 18.
