out what could be a wave of acquisitions following rival America
Online's purchase of Time Warner Inc. The execs say Yahoo!'s strong
fourth-quarter profits validate their independent strategy. ``We
believe our continued best-value proposition is to continue to have
an independent distribution platform that allows us to be fluid and
put in the right things that consumers want,'' said company
president Jeff Mallett. Yahoo!, based in Santa Clara, Calif.,
