phased in on SUVs within three years starting with some 2001 models
as optional equipment, Ford officials said. In designing the
system, Ford is responding to highway crash data that show pickups
and sport utility vehicles, which have a higher center of gravity,
roll over more than cars. Forty-seven percent of all fatalities in
light trucks -- which include SUVs -- result from rollover, according
to the National Highway Traffic Safety
</P>
