<HEADLINE> European Stocks End Mixed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LONDON (AP) -- European stocks ended mixed Wednesday, weighed down by
expectations of interest-rate hikes by the European Central bank, the Federal
Reserve and the Bank of England.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 606 shares in European companies ended almost
uncganged, slipping 0.01 point to 362.92, while the Dow Jones Stoxx 50 Index
rose 0.8 point to 4463.4.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 313 companies from the
countries that have adoped the single currency, fell 1.15 points to 398.27. The
Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index fell 22.2 points to 4649.3.
</P>
<P>
	   The markets struggled amid expectations The Bank of England will raise
interest rates on Thursday, speculation that adversely affected shares of banks,
mortgage lenders and retailers.
</P>
<P>
	   European investors were also expecting the Federal Reserve to increase U.S.
rates on Feb. 2, while stronger-than-expected French consumer price figures for
last year have raised expectations for a European Central Bank rate increase as
well.
</P>
<P>
	   But London shares made late gains amid speculation about Internet-related
acquisitions by Cable and Wireless with the merger agreement between America
Online and Time Warner sending more ripples through European media and telecom
sectors. Frankfurt also ended on the positive side amid late buying of telecom
stocks.
</P>
<P>
	   London's FTSE-100 Share Index rose 13.9 points, or 0.2 percent, to 6,532.8,
Frankfurt's Xetra DAX Index added 21.56 points, or 0.3 percent, to 6912.81, and
the Paris CAC-40 Index lost 31.40 points, or 0.6 percent, to 5,582.50.
</P>
</TEXT>
