<HEADLINE> CORRECTS past tense of "plead" in second graf  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) - Three Buffalo area concrete companies were charged
with dumping high-pH wastes into local creeks, a violation of the federal Clean
Water Act.
<P>
	   PRI Holdings Co. Inc. and Riefler Concrete Products, both of Cheektowaga,
N.Y., pleaded guilty to charges that they allowed high-pH wastes to flow through
pipes and into Ellicott Creek.
</P>
<P>
	   Pine Hill Products Inc., located in Depew, N.Y., admitted to letting waste
drain into a storm sewer system that flows into Cayuga Creek.
</P>
<P>
	   The waste from the concrete companies - that sometimes reached pH levels
over 12 - came from routine "hose downs" of company trucks which were covered in
concrete dust.
</P>
<P>
	   The three companies paid total fines of $210,000 and will pay for the
remediation of damage and a reconstruction of their "hose down" areas to prevent
future discharges.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
