<P>
	   Disney Studio Boss Resigns
</P>
<P>
	   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Walt Disney studio boss Joe Roth, under whom
the company scored two of its three top films ever last year, said
today he is resigning to form his own independent film outfit. Roth
will be replaced as Disney studio chairman by Peter Schneider, who
has been the studio president for the last year. Roth said in a
news release that he had loved working at Disney but feels it's
time for him to pursue a more ``entrepreneurial, independent
life,'' The resignation follows another record year at the box
office for Disney, which was the top film distributor worldwide
with $2.6 billion in ticket sales and No. 1 domestically with $1.24
billion.
