spotlight from flashier technology shares, pushing higher today as
investors shied away from the slumping Internet sector. The Dow
Jones industrial average rose 40.02 to close at 11,551.10, short of
its Monday closing record of 11,572.20. Broader stock indicators
were lower. The Nasdaq composite index fell 71.30 to 3,849.89, and
the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 fell 6.31 to 1,432.25.
