wouldn't have it any other way. But the question now facing the
world's second-richest nation is whether it can keep up the
momentum. Analysts say this year that the economy will finally
return to growth thanks to generous public spending, a recovery in
the stock market, and a bottoming-out of corporate bankruptcies.
But the question is whether dynamic change will give birth to
self-sustained expansion or a return to inertia leads to steady
decline.
</P>
