<HEADLINE> Teletubbies Promotion Announced  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    OAK BROOK, Ill. (AP) -- Ronald McDonald, meet Tinky Winky, Dipsy, Laa-Laa
and Po.
</P>
<P>
	   McDonald's and The itsy bitsy Entertainment Co. -- the distributor of
Teletubbies, the hit TV series for toddlers -- announced a promotion Wednesday
that will bring the tiny characters to the fast-food chain's restaurants in the
United States and Canada.
</P>
<P>
	   The companies wouldn't disclose details about the promotion, but the
Teletubbies are expected to star in Happy Meals giveaways.
</P>
<P>
	   Teletubbies, a British series which premiered in 1998 in the United States,
features four colorful characters with TV sets implanted in their stomachs.
</P>
