<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Utah Avalanche  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PARK CITY, Utah (AP) -- Two backcountry skiers were killed in an avalanche
near a resort north of Park City.
</P>
<P>
	   The couple were reported missing Tuesday night after they failed to pick up
their child from a day care center, said Kim Peterson, a spokeswoman for The
Canyons resort. Their bodies were found buried in deep snow Wednesday outside
the resort's boundaries, Ms. Peterson said.
</P>
<P>
	   The victims' names were not immediately released, but police had said they
were looking for a 47-year-old man and a 41-year-old woman.
</P>
<P>
	   The man was wearing an avalanche locator beacon and had other safety
equipment with him, but the beacon's signal apparently was too weak to be of any
help to searchers, television station KUTV reported.
</P>
<P>
	   Ms. Peterson said avalanche danger was extremely high in the area because of
dramatic temperature changes that can make the snowpack unstable.
</P>
</TEXT>
