<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rise in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    TOKYO (AP) -- Share prices in Japan rose slightly early Thursday following
gains on Wall Street. The dollar fell against the yen.
</P>
<P>
	   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average rose 18.29 points, or 0.09
percent, to 18,695.71. On Wednesday, the average closed down 173.50 points, or
0.92 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nikkei is seen fluctuating in a narrow range amid continued uncertainty
about U.S. stocks, traders said.
</P>
<P>
	   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the first
section fell 4.56 points, or 0.28 percent, to 1,652.36. On Wednesday, the TOPIX
closed down 21.90 points, or 1.30 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   In currency trading, the dollar bought 105.66 yen, down 0.10 yen from late
Wednesday in Tokyo and below its late New York level of 105.99 yen.
</P>
<P>
	   U.S. banks sold dollars to take profits, traders said.
</P>
</TEXT>
