<HEADLINE> Newborn Girl Found in Garbage  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- A newborn girl was in critical condition Wednesday after
being found inside a plastic bag stuffed into a garbage can in a snowy alley.
</P>
<P>
	   The 15-year-old believed to be the mother was taken to the Hennepin County
Medical Center and faces possible criminal charges.
</P>
<P>
	   The girl's two brothers became suspicious when they thought they heard a
baby crying in a family bathroom. Several hours later, the brothers saw the girl
walk into the alley with a trash bag, police said.
</P>
<P>
	   When their mother returned home, she looked inside the bag at her sons'
urging and found the infant, barely alive.
</P>
<P>
	   The woman began blowing air into the baby's mouth until paramedics arrived.
</P>
</TEXT>
