<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-12 23:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Higher at Midday  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo share prices rose Thursday morning following gains on
Wall Street. The dollar fell slightly against the yen.
</P>
<P>
	   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average rose 118.74 points, or 0.64
percent, to 18,796.16. On Wednesday, the average closed down 173.50 points, or
0.92 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   The dollar bought 105.66 yen, down 0.10 yen from late Wednesday in Tokyo and
below its late New York level of 105.99 yen.
</P>
<P>
	   In stock trading, the Nikkei rose on foreign buying amid hopes for an
economic recovery in Japan, traders said. Gains in biotechnology shares
outweighed declines in technology stocks.
</P>
<P>
	   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the first
section fell 0.07 point, insignificant in percentage terms, to 1,656.85. On
Wednesday, the TOPIX closed down 21.90 points, or 1.30 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   In currency trading, U.S. banks sold dollars to take profits, traders said.
Investors are focusing on Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan's speech on
United States economy and technology Thursday at the Economic Club of New York,
they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
